{
  "doc_id": "8871",
  "text": "Much of the research focusing on T1D DC therapy has utilized GM-CSF/IL-4 derived BM-DC generated in the presence of fetal bovine serum (FBS) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [4] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The inclusion of FBS results in BM-DC with phenotypic and functional differences including co-stimulatory marker expression, cytokine production and T cell stimulatory capacity [4, [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] . Two approaches have been utilized to circumvent issues associated with the use of FBS; culture of BM-DC using serum free [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] [CITATION_12] or autologous serum conditioned media [4, [CITATION_13] [CITATION_14] . We chose to focus our efforts on the utilization of chemically defined serum free media to culture BM-DC as this method would provide the least resistance to translation of DC therapy into the clinic.",
